module.exports = {"data":{"post":{"id":"/home/travis/build/simonagren/simonagren.github.io/content/posts/2020-02-28--azurebot-nodejs-part2/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","html":"<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/botframework2-a7f5cecfbea0980063335fbf2dda403f-b70ec.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 46.916666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"extend\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/botframework2-a7f5cecfbea0980063335fbf2dda403f-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/botframework2-a7f5cecfbea0980063335fbf2dda403f-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/botframework2-a7f5cecfbea0980063335fbf2dda403f-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/botframework2-a7f5cecfbea0980063335fbf2dda403f-48538.png 800w,\n/static/botframework2-a7f5cecfbea0980063335fbf2dda403f-b70ec.png 1200w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>In the <a href=\"https://simonagren.github.io/azurebot-nodejs-part1\" target=\"_blank\">previous post</a>, we built the Bot, tested it locally in the emulator, created all resources in Azure and also deployed the Bot to the web service in Azure using ARM templates and Key Vault (<a href=\"https://simonagren.github.io/azurebot-armtemplate-keyvault\" target=\"_blank\">separate post</a>).</p>\n<p>In this second post, we will continue with the Bot and run it from within <strong>Microsoft Teams</strong>. From localhost with the help of <strong>ngrok</strong> and, from the <strong>Azure deployment</strong>. </p>\n<p>Just for fun, we will add an <strong>@mention</strong> in the <strong>echo</strong> when the Bot is in Microsoft Teams.</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Bot Framework in Node.js</th>\n<th>Complimentary post</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://simonagren.github.io/azurebot-nodejs-part1\" target=\"_blank\">\nLet’s begin (Part 1)\n</a></td>\n<td><a href=\"https://simonagren.github.io/azurebot-armtemplate-keyvault\" target=\"_blank\">\nBot Framework 4 ARM template Deploy with Key Vault\n</a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Microsoft Teams (Part 2)</td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"https://simonagren.github.io/azurebot-nodejs-part3\" target=\"_blank\">\nDialogs (Part 3)\n</a></td>\n<td></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<h1>Sourcecode</h1>\n<p>Here is the finalized source code. <a href=\"https://github.com/simonagren/simon-blog-bot-v2\">https://github.com/simonagren/simon-blog-bot-v2</a></p>\n<h1>Prerequisites</h1>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://aka.ms/Emulator-wiki-getting-started\">Bot Emulator</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://nodejs.org/en/download/\">Node.js 10.4+</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://code.visualstudio.com/\">Visual Studio Code</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://azure.microsoft.com/free/\">An Azure Account</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.microsoft.com/office/dev-program\">Office 365 dev tenant</a> - for Microsoft Teams</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://ngrok.com/download\">Ngrok</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoftteams/platform/concepts/build-and-test/app-studio-overview#installing-app-studio\">App Studio installed in Teams</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Infrastructure</h1>\n<p>Last time we created a resource group in Azure that contains the service plan, the web service that runs the Bot, the Bot channels registrations, and the Key vault.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0azure-ba68b21f6f9b3bce82e4c6338033cdbf-edd43.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 500px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 37.6%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"azure\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/0azure-ba68b21f6f9b3bce82e4c6338033cdbf-edd43.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/0azure-ba68b21f6f9b3bce82e4c6338033cdbf-1c603.png 200w,\n/static/0azure-ba68b21f6f9b3bce82e4c6338033cdbf-bb811.png 400w,\n/static/0azure-ba68b21f6f9b3bce82e4c6338033cdbf-edd43.png 500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h1>Code changes</h1>\n<p>There are possibilities to utilize Microsoft Teams context to receive information about the specific Team or channel where the Bot is installed. You could also get information about the user(s) in a chat. </p>\n<ul>\n<li>You import <strong>TeamsInfo</strong> from the <strong>botbuilder</strong> package.</li>\n<li>We will not use the Teams context in this Bot, you have\n<a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoftteams/platform/bots/how-to/get-teams-context?tabs=typescript\">more info here</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/teamsctx-94f4f767ce2fc462db668defb28455d1-61c7a.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 531px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 29.943502824858758%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"teamsinfo\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/teamsctx-94f4f767ce2fc462db668defb28455d1-61c7a.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/teamsctx-94f4f767ce2fc462db668defb28455d1-0a04b.png 200w,\n/static/teamsctx-94f4f767ce2fc462db668defb28455d1-9baac.png 400w,\n/static/teamsctx-94f4f767ce2fc462db668defb28455d1-61c7a.png 531w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 531px) 100vw, 531px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>bot.ts</h2>\n<p>We will add a few imports, and change the <strong>onMessage</strong> method to call the <strong>_messageWithMention</strong> method, that adds a <strong>@mention</strong> if we are in Microsoft Teams.</p>\n<h3>Imports</h3>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\">\n      <pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Activity<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> ActivityHandler<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> ActivityTypes<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Mention<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> TurnContext<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'botbuilder'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3>onMessage</h3>\n<p>In the previous post, we only sent the and echo of what the user wrote. Now we add an if-statement to see if we are in Microsoft Teams or not, and if we are, we call the function to do a <strong>@mention</strong> and pass in the <strong>context</strong>(TurnContext).</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\">\n      <pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">onMessage</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">async</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>context<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> next<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// If we are in Microsoft Teams</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">if</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>context<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>activity<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>channelId <span class=\"token operator\">===</span> <span class=\"token string\">'msteams'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        \n        <span class=\"token comment\">// Send a message with an @Mention</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">this</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">_messageWithMention</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>context<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">else</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        \n        <span class=\"token comment\">// Otherwise we send a normal echo</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> context<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sendActivity</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`You said '</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span> context<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>activity<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>text <span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">'`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// By calling next() you ensure that the next BotHandler is run.</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> <span class=\"token function\">next</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h3>_messageWithMention</h3>\n<p>We receive the context (<strong>TurnContext</strong>) from the <strong>onMessage</strong> method calling this method.</p>\n<p>We first build a <strong>Mention</strong> object, which is an <a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/bot-service/bot-service-activities-entities?view=azure-bot-service-4.0&#x26;tabs=js#mention-entities\">Entity</a>. A mention object consists of three properties:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><em>mentioned</em></strong>: takes a <strong>ChannelAccount</strong>. We utilize the user that sent the message <strong>context.activity.from</strong></li>\n<li><strong><em>text</em></strong>: takes a string. Here we add <strong>&#x3C;at></strong>  to make the <strong>@</strong> and add the users name <strong>context.activity.from.name</strong></li>\n<li><strong><em>type</em></strong>: takes a string. Here we set the type to <strong>‘mention’</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Then we build a <strong>Partial&#x3C;Activity></strong> object. There are plenty of properties, and we will only use a few:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><em>entities</em></strong>: This is an array of <code class=\"language-text\">Entity</code>, and here we add the <code class=\"language-text\">Mention</code> object we created.</li>\n<li><strong><em>text</em></strong>: takes a string. We use the <code class=\"language-text\">mention.text</code> with what the user wrote <code class=\"language-text\">context.activity.text</code></li>\n<li><strong><em>type</em></strong>: takes a string. We use <code class=\"language-text\">ActivityTypes.Message</code> to get the correct value.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This is how the method looks like:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"typescript\">\n      <pre class=\"language-typescript\"><code class=\"language-typescript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">private</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">async</span> <span class=\"token function\">_messageWithMention</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>context<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> TurnContext<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Promise<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token keyword\">void</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// Create mention object</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> mention<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Mention <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        mentioned<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> context<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>activity<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token keyword\">from</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        text<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`&lt;at></span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>context<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>activity<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token keyword\">from</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">&lt;/at>`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">type</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'mention'</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// Construct message to send</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> message<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Partial<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Activity<span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        entities<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>mention<span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        text<span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>mention<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>text<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\"> You said '</span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span> context<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>activity<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>text <span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\">'`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">type</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> ActivityTypes<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>Message\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">// Send the message with @mention</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">await</span> context<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token function\">sendActivity</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>message<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h1>Run the Bot in Microsoft Teams from localhost</h1>\n<p>Okay, cool. Now we need to try this code change in the wild.</p>\n<p>We will run the Bot locally and it will access the Channel Registration in Azure. </p>\n<p>We created an Azure AD Application registration last time we deployed the resources, and the channel registration is using that <strong>clientId</strong> and <strong>secret</strong>. We will use this going forward as well. </p>\n<p>First, we need to change the variables in the <strong>.env</strong> file and use the <strong>clientId</strong> and <strong>secret</strong>.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/1env-c976d5b6d6c30a7d484351ce1f2e3379-4c650.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 424px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 47.40566037735849%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"env\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/1env-c976d5b6d6c30a7d484351ce1f2e3379-4c650.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/1env-c976d5b6d6c30a7d484351ce1f2e3379-7dfac.png 200w,\n/static/1env-c976d5b6d6c30a7d484351ce1f2e3379-7b219.png 400w,\n/static/1env-c976d5b6d6c30a7d484351ce1f2e3379-4c650.png 424w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 424px) 100vw, 424px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The Bot that is deployed and running in the Azure <strong>Web Service</strong> also has these as environment variables in the <strong>application settings</strong>. </p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3appsettings-1e6c5d2287f13e135378f740db5ccdc6-b7508.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 24.844720496894407%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"appsettings\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/3appsettings-1e6c5d2287f13e135378f740db5ccdc6-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3appsettings-1e6c5d2287f13e135378f740db5ccdc6-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/3appsettings-1e6c5d2287f13e135378f740db5ccdc6-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/3appsettings-1e6c5d2287f13e135378f740db5ccdc6-48538.png 800w,\n/static/3appsettings-1e6c5d2287f13e135378f740db5ccdc6-b7508.png 805w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Spin up Ngrok</h2>\n<p>When using a Bot in Microsoft Teams we can’t use <strong>HTTP</strong> anymore, we need to utilize <strong>HTTPS</strong>. And for that, we are going to use the tunneling service <strong>ngrok</strong>.</p>\n<p>This means we can have the Bot running on <strong><a href=\"http://localhost:3978\">http://localhost:3978</a></strong> as normal.</p>\n<p>Spin up <strong>ngrok</strong> and then copy the <strong>https</strong> value.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json\">\n      <pre class=\"language-json\"><code class=\"language-json\">ngrok http <span class=\"token number\">3978</span> --host-header=localhost</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4ngrok-381e53f633a611f5c4c6647c87913593-c51d4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 754px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 40.45092838196286%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"ngrok\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4ngrok-381e53f633a611f5c4c6647c87913593-c51d4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4ngrok-381e53f633a611f5c4c6647c87913593-221a8.png 200w,\n/static/4ngrok-381e53f633a611f5c4c6647c87913593-884fa.png 400w,\n/static/4ngrok-381e53f633a611f5c4c6647c87913593-c51d4.png 754w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 754px) 100vw, 754px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Change Messaging Endpoint in the Bot Registration</h2>\n<p>Open the Azure Portal, go to your resource group and then the <strong>Bot Channels Registration</strong> we created. Change the <strong>Messaging endpoint</strong> value from pointing to the Azure Web Service, to the value we copied from <strong>ngrok</strong>. And don’t forget <strong>/api/messages</strong></p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/5newsettngrok-cb35278aa93e4e06578366affbe001ea-c1714.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 492px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 29.268292682926834%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"news\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/5newsettngrok-cb35278aa93e4e06578366affbe001ea-c1714.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/5newsettngrok-cb35278aa93e4e06578366affbe001ea-31ce0.png 200w,\n/static/5newsettngrok-cb35278aa93e4e06578366affbe001ea-759fe.png 400w,\n/static/5newsettngrok-cb35278aa93e4e06578366affbe001ea-c1714.png 492w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 492px) 100vw, 492px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Activate Teams Channel</h2>\n<p>In the channels tab press on the Teams logo to configure the Teams channel registration.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6teamschannel-f9275ca9dc889bcce2cb8697f3573148-f1cfc.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 687px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 41.48471615720524%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"channel\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/6teamschannel-f9275ca9dc889bcce2cb8697f3573148-f1cfc.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6teamschannel-f9275ca9dc889bcce2cb8697f3573148-6e7f7.png 200w,\n/static/6teamschannel-f9275ca9dc889bcce2cb8697f3573148-50782.png 400w,\n/static/6teamschannel-f9275ca9dc889bcce2cb8697f3573148-f1cfc.png 687w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 687px) 100vw, 687px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Start the Bot</h2>\n<p>You can now start the bot locally with</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"json\">\n      <pre class=\"language-json\"><code class=\"language-json\">npm start</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<h2>Sideload to Teams</h2>\n<p>If you press the Teams icon from channels it will open the Bot inside of Microsoft Teams.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/7tryteams-89a80a8210e4358754d2ba8e8dcf8f4e-a00a0.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 644px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 56.36645962732919%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"try\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/7tryteams-89a80a8210e4358754d2ba8e8dcf8f4e-a00a0.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/7tryteams-89a80a8210e4358754d2ba8e8dcf8f4e-5a1af.png 200w,\n/static/7tryteams-89a80a8210e4358754d2ba8e8dcf8f4e-9c5a3.png 400w,\n/static/7tryteams-89a80a8210e4358754d2ba8e8dcf8f4e-a00a0.png 644w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 644px) 100vw, 644px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Test that it works in Teams as it should</h2>\n<p>Now it should be working fine within the context of Teams. The Bot is running locally and sending messages via the Bot Registration in Azure.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>And if we write something we should get a notification</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/mention-017295c2ec28889364431b50607933f2-a9cf1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 459px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 28.104575163398692%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"mention\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/mention-017295c2ec28889364431b50607933f2-a9cf1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/mention-017295c2ec28889364431b50607933f2-5773f.png 200w,\n/static/mention-017295c2ec28889364431b50607933f2-e46be.png 400w,\n/static/mention-017295c2ec28889364431b50607933f2-a9cf1.png 459w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 459px) 100vw, 459px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>We should also see this in Microsoft Teams</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/mentioninteams-b8b375fb96624468b6071ff018979024-53031.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 799px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 38.798498122653314%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"mentioninteams\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/mentioninteams-b8b375fb96624468b6071ff018979024-53031.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/mentioninteams-b8b375fb96624468b6071ff018979024-5cf27.png 200w,\n/static/mentioninteams-b8b375fb96624468b6071ff018979024-5ef0d.png 400w,\n/static/mentioninteams-b8b375fb96624468b6071ff018979024-53031.png 799w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 799px) 100vw, 799px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>And if we start up the <strong>emulator</strong> again and connect to localhost using the <strong>appId</strong> and <strong>secret</strong> (remember the .env file?) we could see that, as expected, it’s only in Teams that we get then mention.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/mentioncomparasing-f8e0771d077f5e8112d048fac43e0832-c8f4b.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 773px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 59.120310478654595%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"compare\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/mentioncomparasing-f8e0771d077f5e8112d048fac43e0832-c8f4b.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/mentioncomparasing-f8e0771d077f5e8112d048fac43e0832-16cef.png 200w,\n/static/mentioncomparasing-f8e0771d077f5e8112d048fac43e0832-94028.png 400w,\n/static/mentioncomparasing-f8e0771d077f5e8112d048fac43e0832-c8f4b.png 773w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 773px) 100vw, 773px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h1>Let’s install the Bot in Microsoft Teams</h1>\n<p>Oh, this post is getting long…</p>\n<p>You need to know how to install the Bot in Teams as well! </p>\n<p>We will use <strong>App Studio</strong> but you could also create the manifest manually. <a href=\"https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoftteams/platform/bots/how-to/create-a-bot-for-teams#create-it-manually\">Read more here</a>. If you haven’t already installed App Studio, look at the prerequisites and there’s a link.</p>\n<p>This is a generic Microsoft Teams App that we are creating, and then we add a Bot to the application, so the process would be similar if we were adding a Tab.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Start by opening  App Studio and go into the <strong>Manifest editor</strong>.</li>\n<li>From there press <strong>Create a new app</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/manifesteditor-dbbfa3055c3500c1c0348a146e705a47-374d6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 394px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 112.69035532994924%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"appstudio\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/manifesteditor-dbbfa3055c3500c1c0348a146e705a47-374d6.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/manifesteditor-dbbfa3055c3500c1c0348a146e705a47-619e5.png 200w,\n/static/manifesteditor-dbbfa3055c3500c1c0348a146e705a47-374d6.png 394w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 394px) 100vw, 394px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fill in all the details and generate an <strong>App ID</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/9appstudio-85383a590273e1d02d987f2863078d18-cb12f.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 60.22727272727273%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"appstudio\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/9appstudio-85383a590273e1d02d987f2863078d18-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/9appstudio-85383a590273e1d02d987f2863078d18-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/9appstudio-85383a590273e1d02d987f2863078d18-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/9appstudio-85383a590273e1d02d987f2863078d18-48538.png 800w,\n/static/9appstudio-85383a590273e1d02d987f2863078d18-cb12f.png 1056w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>Select the Bot tab. From there press <strong>Set up</strong> and select <strong>Existing bot</strong>. Then pick our Bot from the existing Bots. And we will use <strong>personal</strong> scope.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/10setup-fd61cde90f30618aa4be2d4bf48aa2cd-bb0be.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 749px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 107.87716955941255%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"setup\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/10setup-fd61cde90f30618aa4be2d4bf48aa2cd-bb0be.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/10setup-fd61cde90f30618aa4be2d4bf48aa2cd-dfe50.png 200w,\n/static/10setup-fd61cde90f30618aa4be2d4bf48aa2cd-c966b.png 400w,\n/static/10setup-fd61cde90f30618aa4be2d4bf48aa2cd-bb0be.png 749w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 749px) 100vw, 749px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>As you can see the <strong>Message endpoint</strong> still points to the <strong>ngrok</strong> URL we changed in Azure. </li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/11setup2-5276c5f72ee271cbd9f4348b20823707-94ea3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 800px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 44.81707317073172%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"setup2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/11setup2-5276c5f72ee271cbd9f4348b20823707-48538.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/11setup2-5276c5f72ee271cbd9f4348b20823707-bed0f.png 200w,\n/static/11setup2-5276c5f72ee271cbd9f4348b20823707-5fd34.png 400w,\n/static/11setup2-5276c5f72ee271cbd9f4348b20823707-48538.png 800w,\n/static/11setup2-5276c5f72ee271cbd9f4348b20823707-94ea3.png 984w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<ul>\n<li>We can now go down to the <strong>Test and distribute</strong> tab and press <strong>install</strong>\nThe Bot should work now, congrats!</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Running the Bot from Azure</h2>\n<p>Now we will change the message endpoint to point to Azure again and skip ngrok. Feel free to shut down the local running Bot and ngrok.</p>\n<p>Go back to the Azure Portal, go to your resource group and then the <strong>Bot Channels Registration</strong> we created. Change the <strong>Messaging endpoint</strong> value to the Azure Web Service URL and save.</p>\n<p>This will automatically change the message endpoint in the Teams App.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/changeinappstudio-a0920a1b855e027cba22edcfdae3132d-9090d.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 542px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 54.61254612546125%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px transparent;\"\n        alt=\"setup2\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/changeinappstudio-a0920a1b855e027cba22edcfdae3132d-9090d.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/changeinappstudio-a0920a1b855e027cba22edcfdae3132d-d8d83.png 200w,\n/static/changeinappstudio-a0920a1b855e027cba22edcfdae3132d-65d38.png 400w,\n/static/changeinappstudio-a0920a1b855e027cba22edcfdae3132d-9090d.png 542w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 542px) 100vw, 542px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h1>Final words</h1>\n<p>Remember that we haven’t re-deployed the Bot to Azure. The updated version is running locally. Don’t stress is, we will primarily work from localhost, going forward.</p>\n<p>Have a look at the previous post regarding how to .zip deploy the Bot again, if you want.</p>\n<p>In the next post, we will look at dialogs, prompts, and validation.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/azurebot-nodejs-part2/","prefix":"2020-02-28"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Bot Framework in Node.js - Microsoft Teams (Part 2)","author":"Simon Ågren","category":null,"tags":["botframework","nodejs","azure","msteams"],"cover":{"childImageSharp":{"resize":{"src":"/static/botframework2-a7f5cecfbea0980063335fbf2dda403f-160fa.png"}}}}},"authornote":{"id":"/home/travis/build/simonagren/simonagren.github.io/content/parts/author.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","html":"<p><strong>Simon Ågren</strong> Passionate about SharePoint and Office365. Solution Architect working as a consultant for Sogeti in Umeå, Sweden.</p>"},"site":{"siteMetadata":{"facebook":{"appId":"2263145610597628"}}}},"pathContext":{"slug":"/azurebot-nodejs-part2/","prev":{"id":"/home/travis/build/simonagren/simonagren.github.io/content/posts/2020-02-26--azfunc-v3/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","fields":{"slug":"/azfunc-v3/","prefix":"2020-02-26"},"frontmatter":{"title":"A brief introduction to Azure Functions 3.x","category":null,"tags":["azure","azurefunctions"]}},"next":{"id":"/home/travis/build/simonagren/simonagren.github.io/content/posts/2020-03-02--azfunc-migrate/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","fields":{"slug":"/azfunc-migrate/","prefix":"2020-03-02"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Azure Function migration from 2.0 to 3.0","category":null,"tags":["azure"]}}}}


